Swarnadeep Seth

Design Manager, Writer, and Speaker

About

Diane holds a Master’s in Design from Columbia University and is passionate about building effective teams, and leveraging design to create high growth products.

She currently manages designers at Dot. She has previously managed design teams at Arrow, cofounded a company that was acquired by Parenthesis, and spent a few years as a freelance designer.

Originally from Canada, she studied in Paris and London, worked in Singapore, and is now based in San Francisco. She loves books, yoga, and wine.

item.title: BIO
item.dc:creator: ss13ms054
item.content:encoded:
I am a Graduate Research Associate in Prof. Bhattacharya's group working on the Nanopore Translocation physics. I perform molecular dynamics simulations of bio-polymer capture and translocation through nanopores.

MS in Physics from IISER Kolkata (2018).

Physics graduate student at University of Central Florida (2018-current).

Summer Intern at Los Alamos National Laboratory and recipient of the CNLS fellowship (2019).

UCF Research Symposium poster presentation award (2021).
